      <h1>About</h1>

      <p>I'm Pablo. I build things for the web.</p>

      <p>I started in graphic design — logos, brand identities, the whole Chile-era creative agency thing. Then the iPhone happened, and I pivoted hard into mobile web. Moved to Sweden. Kept going deeper into code.</p>

      <p>These days I'm a frontend engineer who still thinks like a designer. I've shipped login systems for kids' apps at <strong>Toca Boca</strong>, booking flows for cruise lines at <strong>Dreamlake</strong>, and e-commerce for eye-tracking hardware at <strong>Tobii</strong>.</p>

      <p>I work in Swedish, English, Spanish, and Finnish — sometimes all four in the same week.</p>

      <h2>What I actually do</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Build interfaces</strong> — React, TypeScript, Next.js. The modern stack, but I'm not religious about tools.</li>
        <li><strong>Design when needed</strong> — I can go from whiteboard to Figma to production code without handoffs.</li>
        <li><strong>Talk to humans</strong> — I've run workshops, presented to stakeholders, trained users. The "soft" stuff that makes projects work.</li>
      </ul>

